headlines.description: — Ben Simmons shrugged off the boos that rose out of the Philly crowd each time the mercurial guard handled the ball.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets' Ben Simmons booed, loses in Philly homecoming 115-106

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 32 points and eight rebounds, Harrison Barnes added 26 points and the Sacramento Kings won their seventh straight, 113-109 over the Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 32 as Kings beat Grizzlies for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 22 points and the Detroit Pistons snapped a seven-game losing streak with a 110-108 win over the Denver Nuggets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons snap seven-game skid with 110-108 win over Nuggets

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges and Devin Booker each scored 25 points to lead the Phoenix Suns to a 115-105 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns hold on to win 115-105, Lakers' Beverley ejected
